<div class="hero"><div class="hero-inner">
<div>
<div class="badge"><span class="badge-dot"></span>PRO EDITION · v1 · MAY 2026</div>
<h1 class="hero-h">Gym Startup Budget Workbook — <em style="font-family:'Instrument Serif',serif;font-style:italic;color:#00C853;">PRO Edition.</em></h1>
<p class="hero-sub">The interactive, editable spreadsheet version of <a href="/gym-startup-budget-workbook" style="color:#00C853;">Treetop's free 12-chapter workbook</a>. Live formulas. Scenario toggles. Format presets for every gym type. A capital-stack builder that tells you whether your funding sources actually cover your need. The version you'll actually use when you're planning your build, instead of reading and re-reading the static page.</p>
<p class="hero-sub" style="margin-top:1rem;color:#8FAF8F;font-size:0.92rem;">12 sheets · 78 working formulas · data-validation dropdowns · conditional formatting · works in Excel, Google Sheets, and Apple Numbers · single-user license.</p>
</div>
<aside class="purchase-card" id="buy">
<div class="price-row"><div class="price">$99</div><div class="price-sub">one-time<br/>USD</div></div>
<div style="font-size:0.85rem;color:#C0D8C0;line-height:1.5;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">Editable XLSX file. Download immediately after checkout. Single-user license.</div>
<button onclick="checkout()" class="btn-p" id="buy-btn" style="width:100%;">Buy now — secure checkout &rarr;</button>
<div class="error" id="err"></div>
<div class="includes-title">What's included</div>
<ul class="includes-list">
<li>12 interactive sheets covering all 7 cost categories</li>
<li>Live formulas across the whole model — change one input, everything updates</li>
<li>Gym-format presets (PT studio, boutique, CrossFit, mid-size, full-service, franchise)</li>
<li>Tier-1/2/3 location multipliers built in</li>
<li>Aggressive / Realistic / Conservative / Stressed scenario toggles</li>
<li>Capital stack builder with funding-gap conditional formatting</li>
<li>Sensitivity scenarios side-by-side</li>
<li>Glossary + direct links to companion Treetop resources</li>
</ul>
<div class="fine">Powered by Stripe. Secure checkout in a new tab. Your card details never touch our servers.</div>
</aside>
</div></div>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<span class="lbl">What you actually get</span>
<h2 class="h2">12 sheets, designed to be used</h2>
<p class="body">The free workbook page gives you the structure and the numbers. This is the version you build your actual budget in. Every number you change cascades through the model. The scenario toggle reshapes everything — pick "Stressed" and the whole capital-stack analysis updates. Pick a different gym format and the cost ranges update. That's the whole point.</p>

<div class="sheets-grid">
<div class="sheet-card"><div class="sheet-num">01</div><div class="sheet-name">README</div><div class="sheet-desc">How to use, license terms, version, links back to free Treetop resources.</div></div>
<div class="sheet-card"><div class="sheet-num">02</div><div class="sheet-name">Format & Scenario</div><div class="sheet-desc">Pick gym format, location tier, planning scenario. Drives every other sheet.</div></div>
<div class="sheet-card"><div class="sheet-num">03</div><div class="sheet-name">Facility</div><div class="sheet-desc">Sq ft × rent × buildout − TI computed. 10 line items with overridable defaults.</div></div>
<div class="sheet-card"><div class="sheet-num">04</div><div class="sheet-name">Equipment</div><div class="sheet-desc">Per-category buy/lease dropdown. Computes cash outlay + 60-month obligation.</div></div>
<div class="sheet-card"><div class="sheet-num">05</div><div class="sheet-name">Licensing & Insurance</div><div class="sheet-desc">9 Year-1 line items with override-able defaults.</div></div>
<div class="sheet-card"><div class="sheet-num">06</div><div class="sheet-name">Software & Tech Stack</div><div class="sheet-desc">Legacy vs AI-native side-by-side. Computes Year-1 burden including FTE labor offset and savings delta.</div></div>
<div class="sheet-card"><div class="sheet-num">07</div><div class="sheet-name">Staff</div><div class="sheet-desc">Role × FTE × comp × fully-loaded multiplier. AI-native lean staffing baked in.</div></div>
<div class="sheet-card"><div class="sheet-num">08</div><div class="sheet-name">Marketing & Launch</div><div class="sheet-desc">Pre-open + Year-1 marketing budget with overridable defaults.</div></div>
<div class="sheet-card"><div class="sheet-num">09</div><div class="sheet-name">Working Capital</div><div class="sheet-desc">Auto-computed monthly burn × reserve months. Pulls from all other sheets.</div></div>
<div class="sheet-card"><div class="sheet-num">10</div><div class="sheet-name">Capital Stack Builder</div><div class="sheet-desc">10 funding sources. Conditional formatting on the gap cell — red if you don't have enough, green if you do.</div></div>
<div class="sheet-card"><div class="sheet-num">11</div><div class="sheet-name">Sensitivity Scenarios</div><div class="sheet-desc">4-column total-need comparison across Aggressive / Realistic / Conservative / Stressed.</div></div>
<div class="sheet-card"><div class="sheet-num">12</div><div class="sheet-name">Glossary & References</div><div class="sheet-desc">12 key terms defined + 13 reference links to Treetop companion guides.</div></div>
</div>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<span class="lbl">Why pay for it</span>
<h2 class="h2">Why not just use the free workbook page?</h2>
<p class="body">The free page is great if you're early in research and want to understand the structure. This is for when you're actually planning your build. The difference:</p>
<ul class="ul">
<li><strong>Free page:</strong> Read-only structure + reference numbers. You build your budget separately in your own spreadsheet, transcribing the numbers manually.</li>
<li><strong>PRO Edition:</strong> The working spreadsheet with all the structure pre-built. Change inputs, everything cascades. Save 8–12 hours of spreadsheet work and avoid the transcription errors.</li>
</ul>
<p class="body">For a $99 workbook on a $200K-$1.5M decision, the math is obvious. For most operators it pays back the first time you change one input and watch the whole model update.</p>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<span class="lbl">How it works</span>
<h2 class="h2">Purchase flow</h2>
<ul class="ul">
<li><strong>Click "Buy now"</strong> → Stripe checkout opens. Enter card + email.</li>
<li><strong>Stripe processes payment</strong> → you're redirected to the thank-you page.</li>
<li><strong>Download the XLSX immediately</strong> from the thank-you page.</li>
<li><strong>Stripe also emails you a receipt</strong> with a permanent download link, so you can re-access the file anytime.</li>
</ul>
<p class="body" style="margin-top:1rem;">Built and supported by Bill Colbert — Founder, Treetop Growth Strategy. Questions or refund requests: <a href="mailto:bill@treetopgrowthstrategy.com" style="color:#00C853;">bill@treetopgrowthstrategy.com</a>.</p>
</div></section>

